    <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><font size="2"><font face="Microsoft Sans Serif" size="2">

<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Blazzax the Omnifiend</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Blazzax the Omnifiend">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b> 68-68<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font> Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font> Rare_Monster<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font> Doomfire<br>









<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font><br>- Hits for up to 3500 per attack.<BR>- Fire based PBAE (-350) does up to 2000 points of damage and has a radius of 300. He can cast it once per 30 seconds.<BR>- Magic Slowable(Mitigated)<BR><BR><b>Spawn and Scouting</b><BR><BR>Blazzax the Omnifiend can be tracked from just inside of the zone. He is also easy to spot from the Field of Gib, where he spawns. <BR><BR>He is a 3 days spawn.<BR><BR><b>What You Need</b><BR><BR>Blazzax the Omnifiend ranks up there with Fennin Ro as the toughest encounter in the Plane of Fire. Not only does he have a high melee output, but he has a devastating AE attack. You will need a good main tank, at least six clerics in your healing chain, several MGB healers (EE or SOTW) and as much DPS as you can muster. He has been killed by well geared guilds with as few as 40 players, but I would recommend bringing 50+.<BR><BR><b>Preparation</b><BR><BR>Blazzax the Omnifiend is fought at the same preparation area as all of the other Plane of Fire mini-bosses, with the exception of Fennin Ro. To reach this area you will need invisibility and levitation. From the zone in hug the right hand wall until you come to the fortress. The entrance to this fortress is under a tunnel of lava with quite a few mobs in the way. We do not recommend using the lava tunnel. Instead you can climb to the top of the hill on the right hand side and drop down using levitation to the top level of the fortress. <BR><BR>Once you are on the top floor of the fortress head down the stairs until you are at the bottom level. Then head straight to the other side of the fortress. This leads to the Field of Gib. As soon as you exit the fortress turn right until you reach the small hill on the right side. This is the pull location for all Plane of Fire mini-bosses. If for some reason that location is taken you can also use the left side, but the right side has a bit more room to work with, and more flat ground.<BR><BR>If you wish to use enchanter pets in this encounter then you can find them in the tunnel inside of the fortress here. You will need to pull a few guards from inside of the fortress. The tunnel is then in the room to the left hand side. After clearing the guards there, you can pull the Jopals to the raid to be charmed as pets. In my opinion there is no reason to not pull pets for this fight. <BR><BR>The entire raid needs to have their fire resistance buffed as high as possible. You aren't going to resist his AE, but you can partially resist it. <BR><BR><b>The Fight</b><BR><BR>Blazzax ranks with Fennin Ro as the toughest encounter in the Plane of Fire. He hits for up to 3500 per attack, but does not rampage and is slowable (mitigated). What makes him difficult though is his fire based PBAE (-350), which does up to 2000 points of damage and has a radius of 300. He can cast it once per 30 seconds.<BR><BR>Your going to need at least a six cleric healing cycle on the main tank and a decent main tank. As previously noted his melee output is heavy, at 3500 per attack. More importantly though you need to keep the rest of the raid alive while they are taking 4000 damage per minute from his AE.<BR><BR>First and foremost you want to create an MGB healing rotation, as we have for many of our previous encounters. Clerics and druids with EE or Spirit of the Wood need to take turns casting their MGB heals for the duration of the fight. This will help negate this attack.<BR><BR>I also recommend placing paladins in the groups with the complete healing chains. The paladins can use their group heals to quickly heal the clerics after each AE, ensuring that noone ever gets low hit point aggro.<BR><BR>Your best friend in this encounter is DPS. Load up on enchanter pets and drop Blazzax before you run out of MGB healers, and he drops you.<BR><BR><b>Loot</b><BR><BR>Blazzax the Omnifiend drops two loots per kill. He can drop elemental boots and bracer molds. In addition to this he can drop an AC 15 Dex +20, Sta +18, Int +20, Agi +18, HP +140, Mana +140, SV C,M +30 Flowing Thought 6 Cloak. <BR><BR>Additionally he can also drop runes and spectral parchments.<br>

<br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>
<font color=#d2d200>Elemental Boots and Bracelet Molds</font><br>
<A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Cape of Flames%22">Cape of Flames</A><br>

